## Conversation
User invoked /fix-github-issue 5158 (CrewAI Crew.kickoff() hangs after
weave.init()). Then asked to verify the tests fail pre-fix and split into
two commits (failing tests, then fix). This is commit #2 (the fix).

## Root cause
dictify() threads a `seen` set of visited object ids to break reference
cycles, but the `to_dict` branch recursed as dictify(v, maxdepth, depth+1)
WITHOUT passing `seen`, while every other branch (list/dict/sequence/attr)
threads it. Any graph routed through a to_dict-bearing object lost cycle
detection. CrewAI agents/tasks + their litellm models expose to_dict and
form cycles (the integration already excludes crew/agent attrs to break
Agent<->Crew / Task<->Agent cycles), so kickoff input serialization never
terminated.

A TIGHT cycle hits RecursionError -> caught -> ValueError('to_dict
failed') FAST (not a visible hang). The real-world HANG is the
exponential blowup: with `seen` reset at every to_dict boundary, a shared
/ diamond graph re-expands shared sub-objects on every path -> O(2^n).
Both are fixed by threading `seen`.

## Why it surfaced in crewai 0.140 (history)
The hole is original to dictify (a8e49007db, #2680). But dictify was only
ever called via fallback_encode(obj, maxdepth=DEFAULT_MAX_DICTIFY_DEPTH=10)
so the depth cap masked it. Refactor #3784 replaced fallback_encode with
the _encode_dictify ladder entry which calls dictify(obj) with default
maxdepth=0 (unlimited); the crewai integration likewise calls dictify(obj)
with maxdepth=0. DEFAULT_MAX_DICTIFY_DEPTH is now dead code.

## Fix
Thread `seen` through the to_dict branch in BOTH copies of dictify:
weave/trace/serialization/serialize.py and the duplicated
weave/integrations/dspy/dspy_utils.py (identical latent bug). `seen` is a
GLOBAL visited set (never popped): each distinct object expands once,
cycles short-circuit to stringify, shared sub-objects stringify on 2nd
encounter -> O(n). Makes to_dict consistent with the other branches.

Deliberately did NOT change default maxdepth (0->10) or revive
DEFAULT_MAX_DICTIFY_DEPTH: the `seen` fix fully resolves the loop, and
changing the default would truncate deep-but-finite structures for every
dictify caller (crewai/dspy/smolagents/vertexai/gemini/huggingface) — broad
blast radius + snapshot/cassette regression risk for no bug-fix value.

